title: Alphabet Soup
directions: In medium bowl, combine turkey, bread crumbs, egg, thyme, and 1/4 teaspoon each salt and freshly ground black pepper. Cover and refrigerate.
Place leek in bowl of cold water; swish to remove any sand. With hands, transfer leek to colander. Repeat several times with fresh water, until sand is removed. Drain.

In 5- to 6-quart saucepot, heat oil on medium. Add celery and leek; cook 6 to 7 minutes or until tender, stirring occasionally. Add broth, tomatoes, corn, and water. Cover and heat to boiling on high.

Using measuring teaspoon, scoop turkey mixture into balls and drop into pot. Stir in pasta, broccoli, peas, and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer 7 to 9 minutes or until pasta is tender, stirring occasionally.
